This may be indicative of a bug, but I suspect even if so it is 
triggered by your atypical use of DecideRules on the LinksScoper.

The LinksScoper doesn&#39;t *need* to have any rules configured directly on 
it -- its usual method of operation is to simply apply the overall 
crawl&#39;s scope rules.

If a Processor does have rules configured directly on it, then if those 
rules REJECT the URI being processed, the Processor does not process 
that URI any further.

So in the case of the LinksScoper, a REJECT from the locally-configured 
rules means that any outlinks discovered by considering/fetching that 
URI are then *not* subjected to normal scope-testing.

I think that&#39;s leaving the URI-in-process in an unexpected state for 
FrontierScheduler, triggering this error. We can tighten that up but I 
suspect that you don&#39;t want to have special extra rules on LinksScoper. 
Do you really want to *crawl* but not *scope-test-discovered-links* on 
some set of URIs REJECted by those rules?

- Gordon @ IA

